        <article><![CDATA[<p>The Virtual Agent REST APIs allow you to integrate Virtual Agent with any conversational interface that has a routing layer or bot ecosystem that already has a primary bot (i.e. Virtual Agent is a secondary bot). These APIs provide a single request/response end point where you can call both Virtual Agent and Agent Chat capabilities.Â </p>
<p>Virtual Agent API supports the follow key features:</p>
<ul id="virtual-agent-api__ul_y2x_cfc_qmb" style="list-style-position: inside;"><li>Provider authentication and user authorization.</li><li>User ID linking to ServiceNow accounts.</li><li>Transfer or connect directly to a live agent.</li><li>Intent classification in bot-to-bot integrations:<br />
<ul id="virtual-agent-api__ul_n2c_nfc_qmb" style="list-style-position: inside;"><li>Primary bot determines the user intent and sends the intent to Virtual Agent so that the corresponding topic is displayed to the end user.</li><li>Primary bot sends the user utterance to Virtual Agent so that it can discover the intent and return a prediction confidence score. A higher confidence score indicates that the predicted topic more accurately matches the user utterance.</li></ul>
</li></ul>
<p>For more details, please refer to our <a title="documentation" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/quebec-performance-analytics-and-reporting/page/administer/virtual-agent/concept/virtual-agent-api.html" rel="nofollow">documentation</a>.</p>]]></article>
